“Alien Tech” and my thoughts on Neurodivergence 👽 ~
.
Speaking with a fellow neurodivergent friend today, he described it as a superpower. This resonated deeply with me. 🧠✨
.
Being neurodivergent, ADHD, ADD… whatever label they have tried to place on the way that my mind works, which is vastly different than neurotypical. 
.
These terms felt like a stigma when I was young. However, these days I realize how lucky I am.
.
5 years ago I started bio hacking myself. I learned how to use adaptogens like Reishi and Ashwaganda to keep my nervous system grounded.
.
This helped immensely at being able to use this mental energy in a full expression of positivity (lower cortisol = lower anxiety)
.
I started micro dosing psilocybin and the ADHD focus related issues I previously had, are no longer affecting my conversations and relationships. Apparently these focus issues were mostly just low serotonin levels, and this incredible natural serotogenic helps immensely. 
.
After doing the psychological and bio hacking work, I stepped fully into my power. My brain functions optimally, I feel as if I have superpowers.
.
Mostly it is related to how much mental energy I can exert, and how much emotional energy I can withstand. My superpower is that I have seemingly infinite energy, to the point that I can easily become nocturnal (I hardly ever get tired). 
.
This also applies to my natural ability to hold space for people, and have deep conversations for extended periods of time. My just don’t get energetically drained. 
.
Moldavite speaks to this part of me, the nocturnal nature of creative expression. My brain racing through complex patterns. This alienistic mind I have been blessed with.
.
This upcoming year is about stepping through these doors in the full extent of my power. I have learned to not repress my abilities. To allow my mind to fully communicate and express the limits of my creative expression and drive. 
.
Fully embodying my alien self, the multi-tasking, highly productive and highly communicative expression of love and life. 🤍

Life is about perspective. Abundance is a mind set. Why am I so happy? As this photo was taken my friend and I just finished speaking about something incredible. 🖤
.
Our wealth does not dictate our personal happiness. Our mind set does.
.
I have had times in my life where I had the most financial wealth, yet I was the least happiest. And I have experienced the reverse, where I had the least financial wealth, but was the most happiest.
.
Western society over-values financial wealth and over-analyzes the scarcity mindset, which leads us to a life of emotional turmoil, as the balance of our bank accounts dictate our personal happiness.
.
What if I told you, that all of this is unnecessary? That mind set can not only help your rise to success, but can also diminish your days of stress.
.
This concept is not easy, but here is how I prefer to view the world. Anytime in which you are operating from a fear based scarcity mind set, simply meditate on all of the abundance you have in your life.
.
When you put your life into perspective, we have so much to be grateful for. 
.
Whether or not we had more in previous years (the current paradox of the economy has affected many), should never affect your happiness.
.
Speaking with a friend recently who stated that she loves rice and beans, and would be content just eating simple foods.
.
This conversation made me remember how Westerners over-indulge so frequently (myself included) and yet, sometimes the simplest and cheapest of meals can be the most heart warming.
.
Apply this logic to your life, find contentment in the simplest of tasks, and really enjoy the art of simply living, breathing, conversations, and moments of time in which you have to simply exist.
.
We are naturally abundant, because we are alive in a beautiful time to exist.
.
I love you all. My beautiful friends. Thank you for the years of my life in which you all helped me simply exist.
.
Thank you all for the love. 🖤

The face of a man who wins not one, but two live poker tournaments in 2 days. 🏆
.
I returned to the felt this week after taking a break to focus on event management and making Christmas gifts.
.
After my hiatus I have changed my mind set completely. What I have noticed about poker is that the disciplines needed to be a winning player, are the same disciplines that we need to hone in our life in order to be truly happy.
.
This mental sport is a direct parallel to my mind set, and I use my mind set to manifest incredible victories, that are seemingly impossible to achieve.
.
I am playing better than ever, yet, I took a complete break from studying the game. My intuitive reads on people has been heightened, in poker as in life. I have a higher sense of purpose and ability to manifest and achieve what I want and desire.
.
Everything in life is interconnected to our mind state. And sometimes in order to reset my mind state, I take a break, to return later as an evolved version of myself.
.
Ironically, poker has taught me more about Buddhism than life itself. The feelings of impermanence as I allow losses to not affect me mentally, and keep playing perfectly, no matter the outcome.
.
This is true discipline. And this photo, was taken during a moment when I had achieved what seems impossible.
.
I placed 1st out of 98 players in a 5 card variant of poker that I have not played or studied much at all, Pot Limit Big O (High Lo).
.
I outplayed people who have studied and played this game for years. For hours I made perfect plays and adjusted my strategy to my opponents, in a variant that I was learning on the spot.
.
Only a poker player could know how difficult this is to do, and yet, the night before I won a NL Holdem Survivor Tournament as well.
.
The feat of winning one live poker tournament is extremely difficult. To win two in 48 hours is near impossible and requires incredible skill. 
.
This is the second time in my life this has happened. I won WPT Player of The Series the last time it happened. 🤍
.
This is a unique part of my life, that is part of the reason why I am in ATX. Thought I would share a moment in time, in my interesting and diverse life. 🤍

There are two paths in this world~
.
One, the path that is chosen for us, to conform to our place in society, becoming a member or citizen. This path is often the easiest, as it conforms to value structures, allows for financial sustainability, and is the most walked upon road.
.
The other path is to choose individuality through creativity. The path of the artist, musician, writer… poet. 
.
While this path is filled with struggle, we find success in other ways, living and speaking our truth gives us a mental freedom unlike the constrains of societal pressure.
.
Yet, we can also walk both paths. Finding ways to be individuals, while also living within the confines of societal comforts. This is the bridge between worlds. 
.
Presenting my physical representation of this concept, The “Existentialist” Talisman which embodies the free will to choose our reality, and to alter this choice as we see fit.

To choose between being human or alien, stability or revolution, worker or artist… 🤍
.
Dedicated to everyone who struggles when they use psychedelics to open the doors of perception, only to find the difficulty between living in a completely free mental paradigm.
.
We sacrifice that which we love, to survive and provide, and we take great risks on our own survival, to adventure into the realms of freedom and exploration~ 🤍

Hard to convey my feelings for Maui, as I looked through my memories of the last few years of my life in Hawaii searching for words~ 
.
Before speaking on what is happening to the beautiful people of Maui, I will tell a story of this piece, that I created in Hawaii, not knowing the significance that it would have for it’s future owner.
.
I unknowingly put the Burning Man symbol onto the front of the Megalodon Tooth. Then, on the day I finished the piece, I went to a friend’s house to pick up another friend, and she saw the piece and it opened a memory. 
.
She told me that she was there the year that the man ran into the fire, and that she was right near him when he ran. That the trauma of that memory still haunts her.
.
She asked me how much the piece was, and I gave her the best price I was able to… and she added the piece to her collection, as a symbol of grounding to help her with her trauma.
.
My art can symbolize many things, to many people. But the most profound moments are when someone puts beautiful healing intentions into the piece. 
.
And, when I subconsciously create a piece that seems to be created for someone that I have yet to see, or can’t possibly understand, I realize the real reason why I create art.
.
Every single piece of my art is encoded with my own memories, and yet, also encoded with future memories. 
.
I am often creating art while experiencing somatic release, a shift in consciousness through the repetitive movement of my hands with wire and gems… synchronized with my own realizations, or releases of emotions, and blessings of memories as I move forward in life and love.
.
What I want to convey with this story is that when traumatic experiences happen, like witnessing our home in paradise burn, or seeing death before our eyes, that we so often trap these traumas inside.
.
Unable to speak to friends, because the weight is too much for most to bear. Yet, we all need a safe space to speak, to release, that which burdens us. 
.
Holding space for these memories is incredibly important, listening and staying calm. Sometimes we don’t have to say anything, but simply listening is incredibly important.
.

Poker professionals rarely speak of the mental battles that we face, and the actual strain that this game can weigh on our psyche. 

Today I am taking a much needed mental break from work… headed to enjoy nature, water and my loving partner. 

Last month I played 120 hours of poker. It was an emotional rollercoaster, and I am grateful to have completed the most successful month of poker in my entire career. 

Life is filled with waves.

We must embrace the ups and downs,
Learn to feel the ebbs and flows. 

Appreciate the times when everything is flowing,
when everything is beautiful. 

While finding ways to ground and heal through the dark times, the moments that nothing seems to flow. 

I will never complain, I will always just feel, 
I process through my own self, I have always learned to fully feel my emotions without projecting them onto my partner or my friendships. 

What I am learning that is most important, is to embrace change, appreciate the opportunities, and be present through all moments. 

To feel, is to truly live. 🤍

Many years back when I made my first series of collaborations with @roseroadskojima they sold quickly. I wanted to keep one so bad, but could not even afford these collaborations at the time (2013). 
.
Many years later I am less focused on jewelry design. I spend most of my time playing higher stakes poker. While the jewelry market is getting more and more difficult to sustain in, I simply found another source of income using my mind and intellect. 
.
Ironically this pendant became available, for way less than what it originally sold for, and way less than what the piece is worth to me personally. 
.
I remember finding this incredible cornflower blue sapphire crystal at a gem show, and was stoked to set my favorite crystal in a pendant with this priceless Rose Roads cabochon. 
.
Junichi’s work is the best we have ever seen. Glass art collectors have waited on his wait list for years to purchase a single glass pendant. His intricate dot work stands alone as the most iconic glass art jewelry that has allured collectors for decades. 
.
And yesterday, as I opened a piece of treasure, and carefully cleaned and polished it. I feel extremely grateful to be able to buy back a piece of my own history. And steward this beautiful piece of jewelry to the future. 
.
I haven’t completely decided what is to happen with this piece, but I believe I will be re-creating it into a new piece with the same sapphire. All I know is that I am honored to own my second piece of Japanese glass history, and I will be wearing this piece with pride~ 💙
